#: ../../cookbook.rst:2 d38344abf3354a63a3f34898f18ff3ae
msgid "A Voice Chef's Guide to VoxCPM2"
msgstr "A Voice Chef's Guide to VoxCPM2"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:4 252b50dc892249f38eecad07243d783b
msgid ""
"Welcome back to the VoxCPM kitchen. With **VoxCPM 2**, the pantry now "
"includes more languages, richer control, and more expressive voice "
"generation tools. This page keeps the \"voice chef\" framing from the "
"original cookbook while presenting it in a format that fits the "
"documentation site."
msgstr ""
"欢迎来到 VoxCPM 2 的实用示例页。相比前代，它支持更多语言、更丰富的控制方式，以及更有表现力的语音生成能力。这一页主要整理常见写法和使用建议，帮助你更快得到想要的声音效果。"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:9 77ed898a97f741df8e6ab11c7f591109
msgid ""
"Think of it as a companion to :doc:`./usage_guide`: the Usage Guide explains"
" the API and parameters, while this page focuses on practical recipes for "
"getting the sound you want."
msgstr "可以把它当作 :doc:`./usage_guide` 的补充：Usage Guide 讲 API 和参数，这一页更侧重实际写法与使用建议。"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:16 b5fed1344a744b61b4964d9d22a1e49d
msgid "🥚 Step 1: Prepare Your Base Ingredients (Content Support)"
msgstr "🥚 Step 1: 先准备文本内容"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:19 d80522aa0f7f49419181a092efe5dc23
msgid "1. Global Ingredients (Multilingual Support)"
msgstr "1. 多语种输入"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:21 a0fcb41bc2764387b4bdeeaa52be0c5d
msgid ""
"VoxCPM 2 brings a major upgrade to what you can put into the mixing bowl. In"
" most cases, you can simply write the target text directly in the language "
"you want to synthesize."
msgstr "VoxCPM 2 支持的输入范围比以前更广。多数情况下，直接用目标语言写出要合成的文本即可。"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:25 5bbe2401a3244cce86bbe354b87d6c86
msgid "Representative languages include:"
msgstr "代表性语言包括："

#: ../../cookbook.rst:27 2b5677b1d1ca40288a01c56efc480374
msgid ""
"**Asia:** Chinese, Japanese, Korean, Hindi, Thai, Vietnamese, Indonesian, "
"Malay, Tagalog, Khmer, Lao, Burmese"
msgstr "**亚洲：** 中文、日语、韩语、印地语、泰语、越南语、印尼语、马来语、他加禄语、高棉语、老挝语、缅甸语"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:28 2ec24fb4305b4923b17c3e79a93de2dc
msgid ""
"**Europe and the Americas:** English, French, German, Spanish, Italian, "
"Russian, Portuguese, Dutch, Polish, Swedish, Danish, Finnish, Norwegian, "
"Greek"
msgstr "**欧洲与美洲：** 英语、法语、德语、西班牙语、意大利语、俄语、葡萄牙语、荷兰语、波兰语、瑞典语、丹麦语、芬兰语、挪威语、希腊语"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:29 6ecddfac60174c65a836e66f640b7e56
msgid "**Middle East and Africa:** Arabic, Turkish, Hebrew, Swahili"
msgstr "**中东与非洲：** 阿拉伯语、土耳其语、希伯来语、斯瓦希里语"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:33 8465b0be3d844116b0c2663d1c2221aa
msgid ""
"You usually do not need to add an explicit language tag. Start with clean "
"target text in the intended language first, then add extra control only when"
" needed."
msgstr "通常不必额外加语言标签。先用干净的目标语言正文起步，确有需要再加控制项。"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:39 d4695978b81542e58f63a44b89e5d05b
msgid "2. Local Specialties (Chinese Dialects)"
msgstr "2. 中文方言"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:41 582dd112345644a7af72a5093a5450c4
msgid ""
"Cook up authentic local flavors including Sichuan, Cantonese, Wu, Northeast,"
" Henan, Shaanxi, Shandong, Tianjin, and Minnan."
msgstr "也可以尝试更贴近地方口音的表达，例如川话、粤语、吴语、东北话、河南话、陕西话、山东话、天津话、闽南语等。"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:48 24871c9db4c14d3eb7e0fb7bc087d8be
msgid "Dialect"
msgstr "方言"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:49 9e94ca02878e49b9baf8f54d768cdd67
msgid "Example in authentic dialect"
msgstr "地道方言示例"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:50 2f2ce9587bbe412486bdb75261c32051
msgid "Standard Mandarin equivalent"
msgstr "普通话对应说法"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:51 cfb0c26efe5c4ec8839baf2a37591d2d
msgid "Cantonese"
msgstr "粤语"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:52 f6f292f2c2994a29ac931a56bcf3238e
msgid "``伙計，唔該一個A餐，凍奶茶少甜！``"
msgstr "``伙計，唔該一個A餐，凍奶茶少甜！``"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:53 f45b10446b384cfdb9cc1cac9dffad38
msgid "``伙计，麻烦来一个A餐，冰奶茶少糖！``"
msgstr "``伙计，麻烦来一个A餐，冰奶茶少糖！``"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:54 5dc9ab2a66de4406b73beb815392154c
msgid "Sichuanese"
msgstr "四川话"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:55 b513914e52b5468f9b397f8a3baf673b
msgid "``幺儿，哈戳戳得你屋头来噶！``"
msgstr "``幺儿，哈戳戳得你屋头来噶！``"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:56 910c30c928e747d7893576a1458ea982
msgid "``孩子，你怎么跑到家里来了！``"
msgstr "``孩子，你怎么跑到家里来了！``"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:57 1f272a45002148a789bf2be35d120e66
msgid "Northeast"
msgstr "东北话"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:58 cbabff1c427d4b389cb6d5774e07d6c1
msgid "``你搁这整啥玩意儿呢？``"
msgstr "``你搁这整啥玩意儿呢？``"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:59 462062dbddea40229bd42f77f0201f2b
msgid "``你在这儿干什么？``"
msgstr "``你在这儿干什么？``"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:60 1e3fa8bd111849a9975aa0feec7e3812
msgid "Henan"
msgstr "河南话"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:61 8360486cf3e84e439bbdc4884051d102
msgid "``恁这是弄啥嘞？晌午吃啥饭？``"
msgstr "``恁这是弄啥嘞？晌午吃啥饭？``"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:62 4abfec69412a4635b220e04748614ebb
msgid "``你这是在干什么呢？中午吃什么饭？``"
msgstr "``你这是在干什么呢？中午吃什么饭？``"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:64 2c8309c865a6419aa76f0393df1e1a47
msgid "Recommendations:"
msgstr "建议："

#: ../../cookbook.rst:66 76a99998c04841c7b533958f4983a20b
msgid ""
"**Use Authentic Vocabulary:** For the best flavor, your target text should "
"use pure dialect expressions. See the examples above."
msgstr "**尽量使用地道说法：** 想要效果更自然，正文最好直接使用方言里常见的表达，可参考上面的示例。"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:67 e01a70051039479d95a801926fddc654
msgid "Always write in the true local dialect for the best results."
msgstr "始终用真实当地方言书写，效果最佳。"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:68 82f9058101434d4caf79a7919f478332
msgid ""
"**Chef's Secret:** If you do not know how to write in a dialect, use an AI "
"text assistant to translate your standard text into the authentic dialect "
"first."
msgstr "**实用建议：** 如果你不会写方言，可以先用 AI 文本助手把普通话改写成更自然的方言版本。"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:69 d4e394cf3246433ab64e48f46c055e58
msgid ""
"**Keep Instructions Simple:** In the Control Instruction, simply type the "
"dialect name (for example, ``Cantonese``). Adding too many complex voice "
"instructions might spoil the broth."
msgstr "**控制指令尽量简单：** 在 Control Instruction 里写方言名即可（例如 ``Cantonese``）。额外加太多复杂的音色描述，反而可能影响结果。"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:73 3e4423e21ae24d8abc42e4562375f5a5
msgid "3. Extra Spice (Non-verbal Tags)"
msgstr "3. 非语言标签"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:75 7018b02e8ff94ba3926c0a82e3e4f436
msgid ""
"To make generated speech feel less mechanical, you can insert non-verbal "
"tags directly into the target text."
msgstr "如果想让合成语音听起来没那么机械，可以直接在目标文本里加入非语言标签。"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:78 318b5317f8214b52b152aac89b78c809
msgid ""
"Use the **English** tag form with square brackets, for example: "
"``[laughing]`` or ``[sigh]``."
msgstr "建议使用 **英文** 方括号标签，例如：``[laughing]`` 或 ``[sigh]``。"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:85 a7d80ae2d54f439fb4b56fada957a401
msgid "Category"
msgstr "类别"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:86 3fa07924ff704d5a851338a5d67c4cc9
msgid "Recommended tags"
msgstr "推荐标签"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:87 b5d8e4270d494d6b877f8bbece992472
msgid "Laughs and sighs"
msgstr "笑与叹息"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:88 15e855c3203948b28349a40d2ecf9436
msgid "``[laughing]``, ``[sigh]``"
msgstr "``[laughing]``, ``[sigh]``"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:89 51ee9578b2a94c2abbbf949ca87990e5
msgid "Pauses and thinking"
msgstr "停顿与思考"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:90 e14eb288d76425a819e4b5360cd89e2
msgid "``[Uhm]``, ``[Shh]``"
msgstr "``[Uhm]``, ``[Shh]``"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:91 569416dd1e6b4328b96e49e094c58465
msgid "Questions"
msgstr "疑问语气"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:92 9d6860dd8c8442b4803b582a2a299c9a
msgid "``[Question-ah]``, ``[Question-ei]``, ``[Question-en]``, ``[Question-oh]``"
msgstr "``[Question-ah]``, ``[Question-ei]``, ``[Question-en]``, ``[Question-oh]``"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:93 fbfdc0f783e74d0e828634cee41e9130
msgid "Emotions"
msgstr "情绪"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:94 6e186eeece3e49f5910eafdae36279be
msgid "``[Surprise-wa]``, ``[Surprise-yo]``, ``[Dissatisfaction-hnn]``"
msgstr "``[Surprise-wa]``, ``[Surprise-yo]``, ``[Dissatisfaction-hnn]``"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:98 1f35f16ac4e148ef971839dc5007c4b0
msgid ""
"**Kitchen Warnings:** Stick to the recommended tags and use them sparingly. "
"Lowercase tags such as ``[laughing]`` usually work better than variants like"
" ``[Laughter]``. Avoid stacking too many tags into a single sentence."
msgstr ""
"**使用建议：** 尽量只用推荐标签，并控制数量。像 ``[laughing]`` 这样的全小写形式，通常比 ``[Laughter]`` 这类变体更稳定。不要在一句话里叠太多标签。"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:105 4947b3c5b96342209d517b71c6ad5a4d
msgid "🍳 Step 2: Choose Your Flavor Profile (Voice Design)"
msgstr "🍳 Step 2: 设定声音风格"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:108 d9fbaa79b08041e4bf8f0dbeb7a092d6
msgid "1. The \"Build-Your-Own Combo\" (Voice Generation via Text)"
msgstr "1. 仅用文本生成声音"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:110 f919e1d073bd4dbaa8ccf0e6344bde83
msgid ""
"No reference audio? No problem. You can now conjure a voice purely from a "
"text description. Think of it as building your own combo meal by mixing "
"different elements into one comprehensive **Control Instruction**. Both "
"English and Chinese instructions are supported."
msgstr ""
"没有参考音频也可以。现在可以直接通过文字描述生成声音。一个实用的写法是，把不同要素合并进一条完整的 **Control Instruction**。中英文指令都支持。"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:119 638f70e014f44553b50b6d2e8060e046
msgid "Ingredient"
msgstr "要素"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:120 e29f4170503f4f7688fc48b3f7943db6
msgid "Definition"
msgstr "说明"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:121 505c1ddced0640c0b4d4ae03a808a895
msgid "Examples"
msgstr "示例"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:122 0cd5f317ef52426c92eda241abd10923
msgid "**Basic (The Base)**"
msgstr "**身份设定**"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:123 1f3d5385661e4c2fa9edb1cfd69deede
msgid "Core identity such as gender, age, and role"
msgstr "性别、年龄、身份等核心设定"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:124 a71f022cedcc495094d2e2fae9a2569e
msgid "``middle-aged male broadcaster``, ``elderly woman``"
msgstr "``middle-aged male broadcaster``, ``elderly woman``"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:125 543a9414656446a9a72dab8cc73d5765
msgid "**Textured (The Marinade)**"
msgstr "**声音质感**"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:126 ac4e9e2de5be4dcdaf622802f403b079
msgid "Voice quality and pitch"
msgstr "音质与音高"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:127 da34140549bc4473848b458c3308b1e8
msgid "``low-pitched``, ``raspy``, ``magnetic``"
msgstr "``low-pitched``, ``raspy``, ``magnetic``"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:128 a06301072c204dd7afffd4eb9c927948
msgid "**Vivid (The Presentation)**"
msgstr "**表达状态**"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:129 cae5e14b52ec4c34b803959309266862
msgid "Emotion, pacing, and scenario"
msgstr "情绪、节奏与场景"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:130 18b42132fc144dbcbaab42f2d8fff3bc
msgid "``passionate``, ``shouting campaign slogans``, ``historical narration``"
msgstr "``passionate``, ``shouting campaign slogans``, ``historical narration``"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:132 ef6cfa354f574965ab7eee9474d4b049
msgid "Chef's Signature Combos (Examples):"
msgstr "示例组合："

#: ../../cookbook.rst:134 b5cc2845baa1446eb566ef5123a38f8e
msgid ""
"*The Energetic Broadcaster Combo:* "
"``热情洋溢的中年男性播音员，声音较为低沉，富有磁性与感染力，带着逐渐密集的节奏感呼喊宣讲口号``"
msgstr "*播音风格示例：* ``热情洋溢的中年男性播音员，声音较为低沉，富有磁性与感染力，带着逐渐密集的节奏感呼喊宣讲口号``"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:135 bf063f51c58046afa0d66ca26199f025
msgid ""
"*The Historical Narrator Combo:* ``A quiet raspy, elderly woman of a low-"
"pitched voice with a distinct, grainy texture and subtle breathy tremors. "
"Delivers a slow tone at a very low volume, perfect for historical "
"narration.``"
msgstr ""
"*历史旁白示例（英文提示词）：* ``A quiet raspy, elderly woman of a low-pitched voice with a "
"distinct, grainy texture and subtle breathy tremors. Delivers a slow tone at"
" a very low volume, perfect for historical narration.``"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:139 ae231cd0fc3946d59444e359fd3f14ec
msgid ""
"Because of the model's creative nature, every generation can still have "
"subtle, unique variations, a bit like hiring a new voice actor each time."
msgstr "模型本身带有一定随机性，因此每次生成都可能有细微差异。"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:144 21c51ddf3808461a9a0f2595ec5c3cc9
msgid "2. Cloning a Masterpiece (Voice Cloning)"
msgstr "2. 声音克隆"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:146 da18d6c2e1564349aacaf913287e11f2
msgid ""
"Want to replicate a specific voice? Upload or record an audio clip, and "
"VoxCPM 2 will extract and clone the exact timbre."
msgstr "如果你想复现某个具体音色，可以上传或录制一段参考音频，VoxCPM 2 会提取其中的音色特征并进行克隆。"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:149 bb7276dd396b4088a4cb514ecc5a39af
msgid "Practical tips:"
msgstr "实用贴士："

#: ../../cookbook.rst:151 3eb3f78d463342ccba26ad9e9ab43620
msgid ""
"**The 5-Second Rule:** Provide at least 5 seconds of reference audio. The "
"more high-quality audio you provide, the better the clone."
msgstr "**至少准备 5 秒参考音频：** 素材越干净、越稳定，克隆效果通常越好。"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:152 7d21cc88a8c34c428f25d63999a77154
msgid ""
"**Twist the Flavor (Style Control):** Cloning is not just copy-pasting. You "
"can add a **Control Instruction** to change the emotion or speed of the "
"cloned voice while preserving the timbre."
msgstr "**风格控制：** 克隆并不只是照搬音色。你也可以加入 **Control Instruction**，在保留音色的同时调整情绪、语速和表达方式。"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:154 7a157573669e45bc9dcbf0bd849538ac
msgid "Example style instruction:"
msgstr "风格指令示例："

#: ../../cookbook.rst:156 011c3ede93ce42b0a5240335117d1e48
msgid "``speaking very fast, bright and full``"
msgstr "``speaking very fast, bright and full``"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:160 1ad6e85cc6db480483ff6e9f0c35e284
msgid ""
"**Physical Limits:** You cannot perform arbitrary identity transformations "
"from cloning alone. The clone feature is best used for adjusting emotion, "
"speed, and delivery style of the original voice."
msgstr "**需要注意：** 单靠克隆并不能任意改变说话人的身份。这个功能更适合在原始音色基础上调整情绪、语速和说话方式。"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:167 fe19a26ba1174d8c926d89797036b8cd
msgid "Quick Recipe Summary"
msgstr "使用要点"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:169 e32cb5105580445a832a65fec91f0d8f
msgid ""
"Use clean target text in the intended language first; add extra control only"
" when needed."
msgstr "先直接写清楚目标语言的正文；确有需要时再补充额外控制。"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:170 06d36dbbd1c04be691d5d220943c8f96
msgid ""
"For dialects, rewrite the text in authentic dialect wording instead of "
"standard Mandarin."
msgstr "方言场景请用地道方言重写正文，勿用标准普通话硬套。"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:171 43fed77742cc4dd7ad663a532966c585
msgid "Use non-verbal tags sparingly to add breaths, laughter, or hesitation."
msgstr "非语言标签点到为止，用来加气口、笑声或迟疑。"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:172 7c6f35c390764d7897b38b7d8152c8d0
msgid "For Voice Design, combine identity, texture, and scenario into one prompt."
msgstr "做 Voice Design 时，把身份、质感与场景揉进一条 prompt。"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:173 88983d7ca0b84ab7b4aa86ae5febcd61
msgid ""
"For cloning, start with a clean 5-second-plus reference clip and then layer "
"in style control."
msgstr "做克隆时，先准备 5 秒以上的干净参考音频，再逐步加入风格控制。"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:175 a3e59f756c0945c49441903b1d052053
msgid ""
"For the exact ``generate()`` parameters and code-level examples, see "
":doc:`./usage_guide`."
msgstr "``generate()`` 的精确参数与代码示例见 :doc:`./usage_guide`。"

#: ../../cookbook.rst:178 a1d2d562894849d1af5ed39cd323b9e9
msgid ""
"Happy creating. Mix, match, and experiment to find the sound that fits your "
"use case best."
msgstr "多试几次，通常很快就能找到更贴合自己场景的写法和声音效果。"

